-- Property arm of Canada's Caisse fund in first direct Mexico investment - source
-- 
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 07:30AM EDT
-- None



MONTREAL, Oct 8 (Reuters) - The real estate arm of Canadian pension fund Caisse de depot et placement du Quebec will make its first direct investment in Mexico, with a $100 million project in Mexico City, a source familiar with the matter said on Wednesday.

Ivanhoe Cambridge plans to team up with U.S. private equity firm Black Creek Group to build mixed-use developments in Mexico's major cities. The real estate investment unit, which has $40 billion in assets, will spend up to $500 million on its Mexican venture, said the source. An announcement is expected on Wednesday. The first project, two residential condominium blocks, will be built in the capital city in the Cuajimalpa district."Mexico has been on Ivanhoe Cambridge's radar for expanding its presence and investments in Latin America," said the source, speaking on condition of anonymity.